Former Vice President Atiku Abubakar and a National Leader of the APC, Asiwaju Bola Tinubu met at the Akure airport yesterday. Atiku was reportedly on his way to Ekiti State on a working visit when he ran into Asiwaju Tinubu and thereafter   exchanged pleasantries at the airport. In the entourage of Tinubu were Governor Rotimi Akeredolu of Ondo State, Alhaji Kashim Imam and Pius Akinyelure. Atiku was accompanied by a former governor of Ogun State and Director General of the Atiku Presidential Campaign Organisation, Otunba Gbenga Daniel; former Governor of Anambra State, Peter Obi; Capt. Yaya Abubakar and Adamu Abubakar.